		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">A question on bind wounds<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 8:10 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98340902180307&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98340902180307&num=5&post=1&replyto=98340902180307"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=35931">User's Journal</a>  <a name=98340902180307></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35931"><span id=Scholar>Shaladarra</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>30 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>First of all, let me say hello to all you Allakhazamers!&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been using this site as a resource for the past few months and have posted anon many times so I guess you could say I've gone legit and registered!<br><br>I have a question as to bind wounds.  Is it really worth it?  As you can see from my signature (I hope it comes up) I am used to chars like cleric and druid where picking up the Bind Wounds skill was never really a big issue.  Now that I've started a rogue, I'm wondering if I shouldn't invest some points into it and try to get it up.<br><br>I wanted a class I could have that didn't run screaming every time they got hit but I didn't want something like a warrior that was just pure hack and slash with nothing special on the side.  I've been doing the research and I've been hearing people say Rogue's have the HP of a caster so I've got a sinking feeling I may have, yet again, picked a class that can't take a licking and keep on ticking (fortunately if evade is a good skill, shouldn't that mean we don't get hit alot)?  Anyway is bind wounds a good way to reduce down time and is it worth the time and expense (especially considering ALL the other skills we have to worry about training in?)<br><br>Thanks for your help.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Gabrianna Mistmoon - 58<br>HIE Cleric<br>Shaladarra Sowstorm - 46 Druid</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >5 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Feb 28th 9:25 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98340902180307&num=5&post=1&replyto=98341354979578"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98341354979578></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><br>Hello, Rogue a good choice!&nbsp;&nbsp;Buy plenty of bandages and keep it stocked.  You don't need to put points into it.  You may want to put one in it to make you feel better.  I would save it for backstab at 10.  I am a Wood Elf, Rogue and I can bind up to 50% so for me to save a caster mana and to find a place to sit and hide do a bind wound is a good thing to have.  You will find later that you can bind and hide.  :) .  I am a lv 18 and I don't ever recalling the run and scream for a heal.  Bandages don't cost that much if you think about it and if you find someone who is nice enough to use mana and conjour them up Cool.  <br><br>Hide and evade are the same skill so keep up the hide skill.  While you are sitting healing just keep hitting the buttons if your in a safe feeling place.  <br><br>Basically, sit and heal for 50%, or sit and heal for all of your hp .... hummm <br><br>Casters who are oom and people who are close by a hair to passing out will love and welcome you warmly if you have the skill of bind wound.<br><br>Playing a Rogue is fun and exciting!  Enjoy it :)  Sneak and hide .. good scouting skill.  Be proud to be a Rogue .... who can backstab as well as our proud class.<br><br>Hope this helps you in your journey.  <br><br>Gwentoria<br>(18 Lv Rogue)  Soon a 19lv ;)and many more </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
